WEBVTT

00:22.439 --> 00:23.565
[grunting]

00:52.427 --> 00:55.138
-[Tom] The polls are tightening.
-Don't ride the poller coaster.

00:55.221 --> 00:57.557
That way madness lies.
The only poll that matters--

00:57.640 --> 00:58.683
-November fifth.
-Yep.

00:58.767 --> 01:00.643
Would you be saying that
if we were leading?

01:00.727 --> 01:03.396
Ask me when we're leading.
How is your convention speech coming?

01:03.480 --> 01:05.523
It's getting there. Anything else?

01:05.607 --> 01:09.152
Yes. I wanna make an issue of Moss' age.

01:09.235 --> 01:11.780
-Not a chance. Not going there.
-That he is out of touch.

01:11.863 --> 01:14.282
He's looking backward, not forward.
Old versus new.

01:14.365 --> 01:17.118
His ideas, not that he gets
to pay less to go to the movies.

01:17.202 --> 01:19.996
Implied contrast spots, then,
with you doing vigorous things.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.415
-Like, you know, sports.
-I play hockey.

01:22.499 --> 01:23.625
American sports.

01:25.418 --> 01:26.711
[Tom] Hey, honey.

01:26.795 --> 01:30.215
Hi. I'm gonna be late for school.
I will snack there. See you later.

01:31.716 --> 01:33.760
[sighs] It's like that now.

01:33.843 --> 01:36.262
What am I in for
when she turns into a teenager?

01:36.346 --> 01:38.598
You wanna hear, "It'll be fine,"
or you want the truth?

01:40.350 --> 01:41.643
It'll be fine.

01:43.645 --> 01:46.272
What do you expect to find
that we didn't see yesterday?

01:46.356 --> 01:47.357
Which was nothing.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.109
I'm an investigator. I investigate.

01:50.193 --> 01:53.363
Is this boring for you?
'Cause there's a nice empty car outside.

01:53.446 --> 01:56.783
[Eli] Investigator? The "I" in "CIA"
stands for "intelligence."

01:56.866 --> 01:59.285
-I used to be FBI.
-"Used to"?

02:00.203 --> 02:03.456
[sighs] Yeah, well,
I move fast and break things.

02:16.719 --> 02:18.972
This wasn't here yesterday,
all these dots.

02:49.878 --> 02:53.756
-What is that?
-Don't... touch anything.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.427
[theme music playing]

03:05.268 --> 03:07.061
[indistinct chatter]

03:18.072 --> 03:19.073
Your files.

03:20.617 --> 03:21.451
Hi.

03:21.534 --> 03:24.120
I have a meeting with people
who have important things to get to.

03:24.203 --> 03:25.538
As I mentioned last night,

03:25.622 --> 03:29.542
you're being considered for
the vice-presidential spot on the ticket.

03:29.626 --> 03:33.421
Well, let me cut this short.
While honored, I like my current position.

03:33.504 --> 03:35.089
The one with the very important people?

03:35.173 --> 03:38.509
Right. And I'm from Texas,
which Moss will carry as a native son,

03:38.593 --> 03:40.845
so I'd be of no help to the ticket,
geographically.

03:40.929 --> 03:42.972
Geographic balance is a relic concept.

03:43.056 --> 03:46.976
[scoffs] Okay.
Look, I've never run for office.

03:47.060 --> 03:47.894
I don't have the appetite to.

03:47.977 --> 03:51.147
Frankly, I'm not sure
I'd be particularly good at it.

03:51.773 --> 03:55.818
And yet you waited,
despite my rude tardiness.

03:55.902 --> 03:58.863
So you must be
at least somewhat intrigued.

03:59.447 --> 04:01.824
Hey, your surname,
did you have an Anglo father?

04:03.159 --> 04:05.119
No, that was changed.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.580
Would you mind changing it back?

04:08.498 --> 04:12.627
Okay. Well, if this is about exploiting
my Latino background,

04:12.710 --> 04:15.004
-I'll most certainly pass.
-Oh, come on, Aaron.

04:15.088 --> 04:18.341
Don't be so touchy.
You're an excellent fit.

04:18.424 --> 04:21.427
You bolster Kirkman's
foreign policy bona fides,

04:21.511 --> 04:26.266
you're experienced, you're admired
and, yeah, sue me, you're Latino.

04:26.975 --> 04:29.477
Latinos, millennials, urban blacks,

04:29.560 --> 04:33.731
they were all a huge chunk
of the 45% of eligible voters

04:33.815 --> 04:37.944
who stayed home last time,
whining about having no real choice.

04:38.027 --> 04:40.905
What I'm trying to explain to them,
and to all of America,

04:40.989 --> 04:47.620
is that the president, and hopefully you,
are a new and amazing choice.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.250
Let me think about it.

04:52.959 --> 04:55.003
Try thinking about anything else.

04:55.586 --> 04:56.504
Sir?

04:56.587 --> 04:59.424
I've been working on platform thoughts
for the reelect,

04:59.507 --> 05:02.010
but I am president now
and I need to govern.

05:02.093 --> 05:05.596
I know Congress isn't gonna take up our
agenda in the waning months of my term,

05:05.680 --> 05:07.390
but isn't there something we can do?

05:07.473 --> 05:08.516
What's in your platform?

05:08.599 --> 05:12.145
Real tax reform, common sense immigration,
health care for all.

05:12.687 --> 05:15.231
I got a memo from someone at NIH

05:15.315 --> 05:18.901
about the potential way to lower pricing
on certain drugs.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.945
That's good. Let's get someone on that.

05:21.946 --> 05:22.822
Uh...

05:23.489 --> 05:28.286
On the subject of drugs...
Lynn has relapsed.

05:29.787 --> 05:32.373
-She's back in rehab.
-I am so sorry.

05:32.457 --> 05:33.374
[softly] Yeah.

05:34.167 --> 05:38.379
-How are you doing?
-I'm all right. Thanks for asking.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.341
-Do you need to take some time?
-Not necessary.

05:43.092 --> 05:48.181
I just don't want this to become an issue
for the administration or campaign.

05:48.264 --> 05:49.640
It's a private matter.

05:50.349 --> 05:52.518
Does that even exist anymore?

05:53.936 --> 05:57.065
-We won't let it become an issue.
-Thank you, sir.

06:03.404 --> 06:06.741
Okay, we've gotta do something
very important and extremely stupid.

06:06.824 --> 06:07.784
Pick our color.

06:09.160 --> 06:10.953
For the electoral map.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.289
Republicans are red. Democrats are blue.
What are we gonna be?

06:13.372 --> 06:16.751
-Easy. Third color of the flag, white.
-We really wanna be the white party?

06:16.834 --> 06:20.213
-Black, then.
-Connoting foreboding and malevolence. No.

06:20.296 --> 06:22.799
There's already a Green Party.
Gray is ambivalent.

06:22.882 --> 06:26.511
-Yellow?
-The color of cowardice and urine. No.

06:26.594 --> 06:29.472
Purple.
Already used to symbolize neither party.

06:29.555 --> 06:31.015
To what do we owe the honor?

06:31.682 --> 06:32.850
Reporting for duty.

06:33.434 --> 06:35.269
Can we talk in my office?

06:36.104 --> 06:38.356
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

06:38.439 --> 06:41.400
The president assured me
that I would have exclusive prerogative

06:41.484 --> 06:42.485
over hiring and firing.

06:42.568 --> 06:45.530
-Well, if you'd like to call him...
-He doesn't trust me.

06:45.613 --> 06:48.324
Not the case.
I don't trust you, and he trusts me.

06:48.407 --> 06:50.493
Okay, so you're here as what, exactly?
Keeper of the flame?

06:50.576 --> 06:52.328
I'm here to help in any way that I can.

06:52.411 --> 06:53.246
[sighs]

06:53.830 --> 06:56.958
Okay, fine.
You're the new campaign spokesperson.

06:57.041 --> 07:00.837
Your first duty, go demote the old one.
You'll like his office.

07:03.214 --> 07:05.424
-[knocking on door]
-Nope! Go away!

07:07.051 --> 07:10.012
-I've got zip to do.
-All the action's on the campaign, man.

07:10.096 --> 07:12.098
I can't blame Emily for bolting.

07:12.181 --> 07:13.891
The next three months,
the only thing for us to do

07:13.975 --> 07:16.394
is defend the record
and prevent any gaffes.

07:16.477 --> 07:19.897
Hmm. It gives you time to connect with
this daughter you didn't know you had.

07:19.981 --> 07:21.232
How the fuck do you know about that?

07:21.941 --> 07:23.359
[chuckles] Privacy's a last century jam.

07:23.985 --> 07:25.695
I don't know that I have the right to call

07:25.778 --> 07:28.656
this 21-year-old product of my DNA
my daughter.

07:28.739 --> 07:31.409
-But you're gonna contact her?
-I don't know what I'd be getting into.

07:33.369 --> 07:35.621
I bet you're great at online stalking.

07:36.122 --> 07:38.332
-Don't even--
-All I want is the basics, okay?

07:38.416 --> 07:41.752
SAT score, voting record,
whether she's ever been wasted at a rave.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.171
I could be indicted for even hearing this.

07:43.254 --> 07:45.965
It's not like I'm asking the NSA
to draw up her file.

07:46.048 --> 07:47.633
You really need to find something to do.

07:49.051 --> 07:50.470
I think I just did.

07:54.849 --> 07:56.017
Smallpox?

07:56.100 --> 07:58.811
That was the shape of its viral structure,
marked on that wall.

07:58.895 --> 08:00.480
How? The whole place
was scrubbed with bleach.

08:00.563 --> 08:01.814
The researcher would've known

08:01.898 --> 08:03.524
scratching a bleached wall
with anything copper,

08:03.608 --> 08:05.234
like a penny minted before '82,

08:05.318 --> 08:07.612
eventually reveals a mark
for someone to find.

08:07.695 --> 08:10.406
The kinetics of the reaction were slow.
That's why it didn't show up until today.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.825
-Where are we going?
-Fort Detrick in Maryland.

08:12.909 --> 08:15.369
They keep one of the rare stores
of smallpox vaccine.

08:15.453 --> 08:17.580
We get it in time, we'll be fine.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.123
[tires screeching]

08:23.377 --> 08:25.421
Are you fucking kidding me?

08:27.465 --> 08:29.634
-You'll think about it?
-It's not a great job, anyway.

08:29.717 --> 08:32.845
Oh, right. Vice presidency's not worth
a bucket of warm spit.

08:32.929 --> 08:34.138
They cleaned that up. It's "piss."

08:34.222 --> 08:36.057
Garner actually said,
"Bucket of warm piss."

08:36.140 --> 08:37.558
Kirkman can only serve one more term.

08:37.642 --> 08:40.436
You'd be heir apparent next time,
win or lose.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.313
Let me make it simpler for you.

08:42.396 --> 08:44.941
Do you wanna be the first Latino president
of the United States?

08:45.024 --> 08:46.526
-Jesus Christ.
-Oh, my God. Of course.

08:46.609 --> 08:48.861
You don't want people thinking
you were chosen because you're Latino.

08:48.945 --> 08:52.031
-I know you think that's stupid--
-"Stupid" is the nicest word I'd use.

08:54.116 --> 08:57.537
Yes, come in. You expressed an interest
in pharmaceuticals.

08:57.620 --> 09:01.249
Yes, for parasitic worm disease
in sub-Saharan Africa.

09:01.332 --> 09:04.627
Praziquantel for schistosomiasis
costs 21 cents a pill,

09:04.710 --> 09:08.506
but helminths can be fought
with albendazole, costing three cents.

09:08.589 --> 09:10.049
That's what you wanna do.

09:10.132 --> 09:14.053
What I want is for you to get this woman
from the National Institutes of Health in

09:14.136 --> 09:16.347
and learn about march-in rights.

09:16.931 --> 09:18.140
Now would be good.

09:21.561 --> 09:22.562
What's up?

09:23.271 --> 09:25.022
[narrator] <i>President Kirkman</i>
<i>has never mentioned</i>

09:25.106 --> 09:27.108
<i>his transgender sister-in-law.</i>

09:27.191 --> 09:28.818
<i>What exactly is he hiding?</i>

09:28.901 --> 09:31.153
<i>Paid for by Citizens For Family.</i>

09:31.237 --> 09:32.113
Moss?

09:32.196 --> 09:34.240
Super PAC, run by a guy
who used to work for him.

09:34.323 --> 09:37.535
-What do you wanna do, sir?
-Respect Sasha's privacy and ignore it.

09:38.828 --> 09:41.038
-That's not gonna be possible.
-[Seth] This has already gone viral.

09:41.122 --> 09:44.417
All the major networks are gonna cover it.
It's a free media firestorm.

09:44.500 --> 09:47.044
Not only gonna get whacked
by the social conservatives,

09:47.128 --> 09:50.423
but the LGBTQ activists are gonna hit you
for willful neglect.

09:50.506 --> 09:53.134
So, on one hand, I will be accused
of having a secret agenda,

09:53.217 --> 09:54.885
and on the other,
ducking the subject completely.

09:54.969 --> 09:56.846
All because I don't wanna
drag my sister-in-law

09:56.929 --> 09:58.222
through this political maelstrom.

09:58.306 --> 10:01.726
-I'd avoid the word "drag."
-Okay, we're done talking about this.

10:03.102 --> 10:05.479
-I need you to check in with the campaign.
-Yep.

10:08.357 --> 10:09.317
[telephone ringing]

10:09.400 --> 10:10.985
-[Emily] Emily Rhodes.
-[Seth] <i>Emily?</i>

10:11.611 --> 10:14.488
-[Emily chuckles] Ta-da.
<i>-Oh. Congratulations?</i>

10:14.572 --> 10:17.491
Yeah, we'll see. When we have a second,
I'm gonna need some pointers.

10:17.575 --> 10:21.037
Here are the two basic ones.
Don't lie and don't get into an argument.

10:21.120 --> 10:25.124
Okay, well, I assume you're calling about
the sister-in-law spot. Fucking Moss.

10:25.207 --> 10:27.335
He's an unprincipled, ego-drunk choad.

10:27.418 --> 10:29.587
Yeah, well,
he and the president were friends.

10:29.670 --> 10:32.465
<i>-I never trusted him.</i>
-Okay, great. Then you win.

10:32.548 --> 10:35.551
Naivete is among your elemental charms.

10:36.177 --> 10:37.637
<i>Did you know about Sasha?</i>

10:37.720 --> 10:39.263
Yeah, she and the First Lady
were pretty close.

10:39.347 --> 10:41.349
It was really hard on Alex
when she moved to Paris.

10:41.432 --> 10:44.185
But, you know,
she never wanted to be in the spotlight.

10:44.268 --> 10:46.187
Well, sadly, that's all over now.

10:46.270 --> 10:48.105
That's what I'm on my way
to talk to the president about now.

10:48.189 --> 10:50.566
I'll catch you later. Okay.

10:51.984 --> 10:53.694
[knocking on door]

10:53.778 --> 10:56.572
-[Isabel] Hi.
-Hi. I'm Kasey from the NIH.

10:57.406 --> 10:58.532
Isabel.

10:58.616 --> 11:01.994
[coughs] It's okay,
I don't have meningitis.

11:02.078 --> 11:05.081
Jury's still out on lupus,
but that's not contagious, so...

11:06.874 --> 11:10.336
You're here to educate me
on march-in rights.

11:10.419 --> 11:14.799
Okay. So, a significant portion
of drug research and development

11:14.882 --> 11:19.845
is actually funded by federal grants
to university labs and foundations.

11:19.929 --> 11:22.681
The Bayh-Dole Act
allows pharmaceutical companies

11:22.765 --> 11:26.811
to then purchase patents
on any marketable medications that result.

11:26.894 --> 11:30.481
And charge whatever they like for them,
usually exorbitantly.

11:30.564 --> 11:34.193
With their usual justification
of R&D costs. Complete bullshit.

11:34.276 --> 11:37.113
Yeah. However, tucked away in Bayh-Dole

11:37.196 --> 11:40.074
is a provision allowing
the federal government to march in

11:40.157 --> 11:43.327
and take away patents for drugs
developed using federal dollars

11:43.411 --> 11:46.247
that aren't reaching an adequate portion
of the patients who need them.

11:46.831 --> 11:48.958
Because they cost too fucking much.

11:49.041 --> 11:51.877
[grunts] Are we allowed
to swear like that?

11:52.420 --> 11:54.255
The FBI's not gonna burst
through the door.

11:54.338 --> 11:55.464
[chuckles]

11:55.548 --> 12:00.886
So you're saying that the president
possesses previously legislated authority

12:00.970 --> 12:02.930
to force certain drug prices down?

12:03.013 --> 12:03.931
Yes.

12:04.014 --> 12:05.558
Fuckin' A.

12:06.392 --> 12:08.436
She's received death threats.
Death threats!

12:08.519 --> 12:10.396
That harassment isn't gonna stop
until you make it.

12:10.479 --> 12:13.190
A statement alone is not gonna do it.
You have to bring her here.

12:13.274 --> 12:15.651
Normalize her
to neutralize this as a talking point.

12:16.277 --> 12:17.945
She doesn't deserve any of this.

12:20.698 --> 12:22.658
Fine. You're right. I'll invite her.

12:22.741 --> 12:26.120
Moss is gonna keep this up
until we bloody his nose.

12:27.079 --> 12:29.707
I wanna leak
that he's carrying the Alzheimer's gene.

12:29.790 --> 12:30.749
Oh, my God.

12:30.833 --> 12:33.627
-We can't make up something like that.
-Not making it up.

12:33.711 --> 12:37.673
You know the AIPAC event
that all three campaigns did last week?

12:37.756 --> 12:41.385
Our team came in to set up
while they were clearing away after Moss,

12:41.469 --> 12:42.928
-and I swiped his spoon.
-[Emily] I don't believe this.

12:43.012 --> 12:46.599
I had it tested for DNA.
I think the result speaks for itself.

12:46.682 --> 12:47.641
That's gene theft.

12:47.725 --> 12:50.603
Illegal in only eight states,
none of them being Virginia.

12:50.686 --> 12:54.064
And unethical in all 50,
and a complete violation of his privacy.

12:54.148 --> 12:57.568
Sort of like what they did to Sasha,
only this is actually relevant.

12:57.651 --> 12:58.486
Oh, come on.

12:58.569 --> 13:01.280
A 70-year-old man
running for a four-year term,

13:01.363 --> 13:04.909
with a 12 times greater-than-normal
risk of cognitive decline.

13:04.992 --> 13:08.245
You think the American people
really want an Alzheimer's-addled Moss

13:08.329 --> 13:10.664
answering the 3:00 a.m. crisis call?

13:10.748 --> 13:12.708
This is absolutely fair game.

13:12.791 --> 13:15.002
And what's next?
A break-in at his cardiologist's?

13:15.085 --> 13:17.379
The American people
have the right to know.

13:18.797 --> 13:21.926
And Moss has a right not to,
if that's his choice.

13:22.009 --> 13:23.928
We are certainly not
going to be the people

13:24.011 --> 13:26.096
to make such a personal decision for him.

13:26.180 --> 13:28.098
I wouldn't want anyone making it for me.

13:28.182 --> 13:30.059
I forbid this. That's final. Thank you.

13:32.019 --> 13:35.231
Mr. Harper, Penny's school's calling
for the president.

13:35.314 --> 13:37.316
-Can he be interrupted?
-[Mars] What's it about?

13:37.399 --> 13:39.109
May I ask what this is concerning?

13:40.819 --> 13:42.154
[clears throat]

13:43.155 --> 13:44.657
This is Chief of Staff Harper.

13:47.826 --> 13:51.830
I see. Thank you for informing us.
I'll let the president know.

13:53.207 --> 13:54.625
Good day not to be you.

13:55.501 --> 13:58.420
That's most days, but, uh, yeah.

14:00.673 --> 14:01.757
What now?

14:04.343 --> 14:06.720
-Penny's school called.
-Is she all right?

14:06.804 --> 14:08.597
Nothing alarming. At least, I wouldn't...

14:08.681 --> 14:11.934
Not that I'd...
I mean, it's part of... You know...

14:12.017 --> 14:13.185
Not so far.

14:14.853 --> 14:16.063
It's a bit awkward.

14:16.146 --> 14:18.774
I would say the awkwardness
is verging on profound.

14:22.152 --> 14:26.448
Penny got her period. So... that.

14:28.367 --> 14:29.285
Hmm.

14:31.287 --> 14:34.915
Two middle-aged men talking about
one of their daughter's first period.

14:35.708 --> 14:37.626
What could be awkward about that?

14:39.587 --> 14:41.672
-I'm not sure what I--
-I think you just leave.

14:55.311 --> 14:56.979
She's growing up, honey.

14:59.982 --> 15:01.108
She's growing up.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.236
[Hannah] Yeah, Dianne, we're fine.

15:04.904 --> 15:08.949
As transmissible as smallpox is,
the vaccine is completely effective

15:09.033 --> 15:11.535
if taken within
the 12-day incubation period

15:11.619 --> 15:14.788
that someone nicer would've
told me about sooner, but he didn't.

15:15.581 --> 15:18.709
Yeah. She wants to know how this guy
got his hands on smallpox.

15:18.792 --> 15:22.004
He didn't. He ordered separate pieces
of DNA and put it together.

15:22.087 --> 15:24.882
Which is supposed to be
closely monitored and isn't. Ergo...

15:25.507 --> 15:26.508
Did you get that?

15:27.343 --> 15:32.514
Dr. Mays believes the researcher isolated
the contagion section of smallpox DNA,

15:32.598 --> 15:35.517
and then via CRISPR,
he inserted it into the bird flu virus,

15:35.601 --> 15:39.521
which accounts for its sudden
greater communicability.

15:40.731 --> 15:42.650
Tell her we're going to Toronto.

15:43.651 --> 15:46.528
There's been an outbreak
at an OB-GYN clinic in Toronto.

15:46.612 --> 15:48.822
We're gonna head... Yes, Dianne.

15:49.907 --> 15:52.785
Yeah, I got it. Okay. Goodbye.

15:53.661 --> 15:54.954
What was that?

15:55.037 --> 15:59.667
She's just reminding me I'm CIA now,
whose stock-in-trade is stealth.

15:59.750 --> 16:02.878
So she would prefer
that I go about my business

16:02.962 --> 16:07.508
without attracting
the attention of the local constabulary.

16:08.842 --> 16:09.677
[clamoring]

16:09.760 --> 16:11.220
-[Seth] Philip!
-[Philip] Thank you, Seth.

16:11.303 --> 16:13.973
Why has the president not mentioned
his sister-in-law before?

16:14.056 --> 16:16.767
Not mentioning something is not
the same thing as not mentioning it.

16:16.850 --> 16:18.477
If that's not too Zen koan.

16:18.560 --> 16:19.895
-Seth!
-[Seth] Yes, Dennis.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.772
Was President Kirkman
trying to conceal it?

16:21.855 --> 16:24.358
"It" is a human being with a name,
which is private.

16:24.441 --> 16:26.610
The president's intent being
to respect said privacy,

16:26.694 --> 16:28.278
not to try to conceal anything. Yeah.

16:28.362 --> 16:30.656
Seth, what's the president's position
on transgender rights?

16:30.739 --> 16:32.116
The president supports all human rights.

16:32.199 --> 16:35.119
Seth! Is the president's position
on transgender rights

16:35.202 --> 16:36.704
influenced by his sister-in-law?

16:36.787 --> 16:38.497
It was just asked
what that position even was.

16:38.580 --> 16:39.999
Obviously, a position you can't identify

16:40.082 --> 16:43.502
can't magically be brought into being
just because of a family relation.

16:45.587 --> 16:47.381
That made sense in my head
before I said it.

16:47.464 --> 16:49.091
-[reporters clamoring]
-Gary Lee.

16:59.768 --> 17:02.521
